Find all non-zero real numbers $x,y,z$ which satisfy the system of equations: \begin{align}
(x^2+xy+y^2)(y^2+yz+z^2)(z^2+zx+x^2)&=xyz,\\(x^4+x^2y^2+y^4)(y^4+y^2z^2+z^4)(z^4+z^2x^2+x^4)&=x^3y^3z^3
\end{align} It's an indian olympiad question. Can you guys help me out in solving it please ? edit: I have tried to write the first equation as: $(\frac{x^3-y^3}{x-y})(\frac{y^3-z^3}{y-z})(\frac{z^3-x^3}{z-x})$ = xyz And second equation as: $(\frac{x^6-y^6}{x^2-y^2})(\frac{y^6-z^6}{y^2-z^2})(\frac{z^6-x^6}{z^2-x^2}) = x^3y^3z^3$ Then divided the two to get: $(\frac{x^3+y^3}{x+y})(\frac{y^3+z^3}{y+z})(\frac{z^3+x^3}{z+x}) = x^2y^2z^2$ After that I have no sign what to do??

